author: d3vd (amy)
content:
"unreturned"

i love you in silence, in shadows, in dreams,
in moments that crack at the quietest seams.
you smile like the world never hurt you at all,
while i build my heart just to watch it fall.

you’ll never be mine — i’ve known from the start,
still, somehow, you live in the beat of my heart.
you laugh, and i flinch, like a ghost of a touch,
it’s cruel how i feel something you never clutch.

i lie to myself: one day, maybe so,
but deep down i whisper, you’ll never know.
not like i do — this ache, this flame,
this wishing i wasn’t the one to blame.

and i’m scared — not of now, but the years ahead,
where you still live in my heart, rent-free in my head.
what if i never move on from this pain?
what if loving you carves me in vain?

still, i love — without hope, without claim or demand,
with a bruised little heart and a trembling hand.
you’ll never be mine, and i’ll never be free,
but i’ll keep loving you... quietly.
